'''Bank paper''' is a thin strong writing [[paper]] of less than 50g/m<sup>2</sup>. It is commonly used for typewriting and correspondence.

The term is also used for [[securities]] that are issued by [[bank]]s, instead of governments. See also [[commercial paper]], securities issued by [[corporations]].

