{{Infobox oil refinery | name = Baton Rouge Refinery | image = File:Exxon Mobil oil refinery - Baton Rouge, Louisiana.jpg | image alt = <!-- See WP:Alternative text for images --> | caption = Baton Rouge Refinery seen from the [[Louisiana State Capitol]], looking north | location_map = Louisiana | location_map_width = | location_map_text = Location of the Baton Rouge Refinery in Louisiana, United States | coordinates = {{coord|30|29|1|N|91|10|50|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = United States | province = [[Louisiana]] | city = [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana|Baton Rouge]] | operator = | owner = [[ExxonMobil]] | founded = {{Start date|1909}} | closure = | capacity = | capacity bbl/d = 503000 | employees = 4000 | ref units = | oil tank = | oil refining center = }} [[ExxonMobil]]'s '''Baton Rouge Refinery''' in [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]] is the fourth-largest [[oil refinery]] in the [[United States]] and twelfth-largest in the world,<ref>[[List of oil refineries#World.27s largest refineries]]</ref> with an input capacity of {{convert|502500|oilbbl|m3}} per day as of January 1, 2016.<ref>http://cdn.exxonmobil.com/~/media/global/files/us-refineries/2016_brrf_fact_sheet.pdf</ref> The refinery is the site of the first commercial [[Fluid catalytic cracking|fluid catalytic cracking plant]] that began processing at the refinery on May 25, 1942.
[[Standard Oil]] first erected the refinery in 1909. Today's facility is part of a complex made of nine individual plants across the region. The main plant is located on the east bank of the [[Mississippi River]]. There are about 6,300 workers spread across these sites, including 4,000 direct [[employee]]s (the rest are [[general contractor|contractors]]).
Genesis Energy LP recently invested $125 million to improve ExxonMobil's existing assets in the Baton Rouge area. The investment includes plans to build an 18-mile, 20-inch diameter crude oil pipeline that connects Genesis Energy's Port Hudson terminal, to ExxonMobil's Baton Rouge refinery.<ref>{{cite news|last=Perilloux|first=Gary|title=Genesis Energy To Invest $125 Million In Baton Rouge Area Infrastructure Project |url=http://www.louisianaeconomicdevelopment.com/led-news/news-releases/genesis-energy-to-invest-$125-million-in-baton-rouge-area-infrastructure-project.aspx?c=News%20Releases&id=39|accessdate=2013-03-05|newspaper=Louisiana Economic Development|date=2013-02-04}}</ref> The Baton Rouge refinery's tank farm has a capacity of 502,500 barrel-per-day (bpd).<ref>{{cite news|last=Hays|first=Kristen|title=Genesis Energy expanding crude delivery to Exxon Baton Rouge|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/02/04/update-1-genesis-batonrouge-crude-idUSL1N0B45V520130204|accessdate=2013-03-05|newspaper=Reuters|date=2012-02-04}}</ref> [[File:ExxonMobil Baton Rouge.jpg|thumb|center|600px|The refinery seen from the Capitol tower]]
